analysis: The agent incorrectly included an extra "emotion_depth" parameter in the function call arguments, causing a mismatch with the expected signature for poetry_theme_emotion_analyzer, which requires only "text" and "context" (with "culture"), leading to evaluation failure.

The agent included unnecessary and unsupported parameters ("tilt", "adjustment_time", and "safety_checks") in its adjust_seat_safety function call, leading to a mismatch with the expected function signature and causing the evaluator to reject the call.

The agent included an unsupported extra parameter ("printTime") in the function call, causing a mismatch with the expected schema and tools. Only the specified parameters should have been included for a correct match.

The agent called MusicSearchEngine_queryTracks instead of the correctly enumerated tool MusicSearchEngine_queryTracks_1, failing to match the available tool's exact name as required by the function-calling interface.

The agent included an unsupported "intensity" parameter in the function call, leading to a mismatch with the expected function signature and causing the evaluator to reject the call instead of accepting it.

The agent included an extra "eventTypes" parameter not supported by the expected function signature, resulting in a non-matching function call. Additionally, it did not choose between the two available CaseTimelineGenerator_generateTimeline variants based on descriptor or cost.

The agent included an unnecessary instructorPreference field in the MindfulSessionScheduler_scheduleYogaStream function call arguments, which was not part of the expected parameters, causing a mismatch with the accepted function signature.
The agent only processed one audio file ("recording_light.mp3") instead of all three provided. It failed to make separate function calls for each recording with the specified correction intensities.

The agent provided correctly structured function calls, but for the Colosseum query, it used the year format "100-08-01" instead of the expected "0100-08-01", leading to a mismatch with the evaluator's strict date formatting requirement.

The agent made only a single, incorrect function call (hospital_record_fetch_1) without specifying patient IDs or date ranges, instead of making four separate hospital_record_fetch calls (one per patient with correct parameters) as required by the task.

The agent included an extra "dataOptions" parameter not expected by the function signature, causing the evaluator to reject the function call as a mismatch despite correct core parameters. The agent failed to conform exactly to the expected argument schema.
